-- Canada Doesn't Give a `Blank Check' to Foreign Takeovers, Harper Says
-- Theophilos Argitis
-- 2010-09-20T18:37:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/canada-doesn-t-give-a-blank-check-to-foreign-takeovers-harper-says.html

          
          
             Canadian Prime Minister Stephen
Harper said his government hasn’t given a “blank check” to
foreign takeovers, saying there are laws in place to review
acquisitions of companies such as Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan.  
 Harper made the comments today in Parliament.  
